    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @odecharette Thanks for opening this issue. \r\n\r\nFirst your records need to have a `_geoloc` attribute with their positions so that the engine understands where those records are geolocated. Then you need to configure the requests to use the IP for geolocating the user. This time you have to set it using the constructor of InstantSearch:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n  /* all credentials etc. */\r\n  searchParameters: {\r\n    aroundLatLngViaIP: true,\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou should use that in the Service definition. Let me know how it works for you.\r\n\r\nAs a side note, we also have a [brand new integration for Angular](https://algolia.gitbooks.io/angular-instantsearch) in beta. Have a look, we hope it'll help even more than the InstantSearch.js + Angular guide",
